;; futon0/data/cron-jobs.edn — Canonical registry of installed cron jobs on this machine.
;;
;; Purpose: a single source-of-truth for cron jobs the futon stack relies on, so the
;; operator doesn't lose track of them. Each entry records what the job does, when it
;; runs, where its logs go, and the contract/mission it serves.
;;
;; Lifecycle (per Joe directive 2026-05-21 "make an index of such cron jobs in Arxana
;; so I don't lose track of them — the list can go right into the root of arxana://"):
;;   - This file is the canonical, operator-readable form. Edit by hand or via tools.
;;   - A typed hyperedge `arxana/index/cron-jobs` in the authoritative Futon1b
;;     substrate mirrors this content
;;     for runtime queryability. To refresh the mirror after editing this file, run
;;     the script `bb scripts/upsert_cron_jobs_index.bb` from futon0 (TBD; for now,
;;     manual re-upsert).
;;   - The crontab itself lives at `crontab -l`; this registry is a documentation
;;     layer above it. The crontab's comment header points back here.
;;
;; Schema (v1):
;;   :schema-version    integer
;;   :installed-by      who first laid this down
;;   :installed-at      ISO-8601
;;   :registry-purpose  human-readable summary
;;   :jobs              vector of job maps with shape:
;;     :job-id         keyword unique identifier
;;     :schedule       crontab schedule expression
;;     :command        the literal command line
;;     :log-path       absolute path to log file
;;     :purpose        what the job does in operator terms
;;     :owner-mission  mission doc(s) this job serves
;;     :contract-row   contract row (R-criterion / F-criterion / etc.) the job satisfies
;;     :installed-at   ISO-8601 of when this entry landed
;;     :installed-by   agent / operator who added it
;;     :status         :active | :disabled | :retired

